Definition at line 41 of file NavMessage.h.

enum NavMessage::ReplyStatus
 

Enum for general reply statuses.

NAV_STATUS_REQUEST_SPECIFIC_MASK is not a status but a mask to see if a status code is request specific or not. Status codes with the high bit set, 0x80-0xff, is request specific.

Enumeration values:
NAV_STATUS_OK 
NAV_STATUS_NOT_OK 
NAV_STATUS_REQUEST_TIMEOUT 
NAV_STATUS_PARAM_REQ_NOT_FIRST 
NAV_STATUS_OUTSIDE_MAP 
NAV_STATUS_PROTOVER_NOT_SUPPORTED 
NAV_STATUS_OUTSIDE_ALLOWED_AREA 
NAV_STATUS_NO_TRANSACTIONS_LEFT 
NAV_STATUS_REQUEST_SPECIFIC_MASK
